			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">From one that has been there, and has the stats - 
<br />

<br />
10 regular adventures in a zone = +2 hp/ +2 mana
<br />

<br />
For every +10 hp / +10 mana, you get +1 all stats and +1 all saves.
<br />

<br />
You do not need to do 50 in a zone.  You only need intervals of 10 in ANY zone, and any five such intervals.
<br />

<br />
When I had 12 in Butcherblock, 10 in North Ro and 30 in Everfrost, my adventure stone was +1 all stats, +1 all saves and +10 hp / +10 mana.
<br />

<br />
Be aware, you need to hail the proper NPC to get the upgrade to your stone.  You can hail them every 2 adventures as far as I can tell.  I tend to wait until I have intervals of 10.
<br />

<br />
The first NPC you hail wil be near your camp.  After you have done 20 or so in a zone, you wil be sent to another NPC.  Example, for Everfrost, I now have to go to Qeynos Hills and hail an NPC outside of Blackburrow for my upgrades.
<br />

<br />
-wogai<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=635719" target="_blank" class="postlink">Wogai Goh - Veeshan </a>
<br />
No, I don't mind dying.  That's why we have clerics.</span><span class="gentblsmall"></span></td>
